Bluetongue, Turkey
--------------------
Information received on [and dated] 31 Oct 2014 from Prof. Dr Irfan Erol, Director General of Food and Control, Directorate of Food and Control, Ministry of Food, Agriculture and Livestock, Ankara, Turkey

Summary
Report type: immediate notification
Date of start of the event: 8 Oct 2014
Date of pre-confirmation of the event: 16 Oct 2014
Reason for notification: reoccurrence of a listed disease
Date of previous occurrence: 22 Sep 2014
Manifestation of disease: clinical disease
Causal agent: Bluetongue virus
Serotype: 4
Nature of diagnosis: clinical, laboratory (advanced)
This event pertains to the whole country.

New outbreaks (3)
Summary of outbreaks: Total outbreaks: 3
Total animals affected:
Species / Susceptible / Cases / Deaths / Destroyed / Slaughtered
Sheep / 328 / 8 / 3 / 0 / 0

Outbreak statistics [rates apparent, expressed as percentages]
Species / Morbidity rate / Mortality rate / Case fatality rate / Proportion susceptible animals lost*
Sheep / 2.44 / 0.91 / 37.50 / 0.91
* Removed from the susceptible population through death, destruction, and/or slaughter

[Note: The 3 outbreaks were located in the following provinces: Balikesir and Canakkale. See details of each outbreak in the URL above. - Mod.CRD]

Epidemiology
Source of the outbreak(s) or origin of infection: contact with infected animals(s) at grazing/watering

Control measures
Measures applied: control of arthropods; quarantine; movement control inside the country; disinfection of infected premises/establishment(s); no treatment of affected animals; vaccination in response to the outbreak(s).
Administrative division / Species / Total vaccinated / Details
Canakkale / Sheep / 61 700 / -
Balikesir / Sheep / 49 074 / -
Measures to be applied: no other measures

Diagnostic test results:
Laboratory name and type / Species / Test / Test date / Result
Etlik Veterinary Control Central Research Institute (National laboratory) / Sheep / real-time PCR / 16 Oct 2014 / Positive
Etlik Veterinary Control Central Research Institute (National laboratory) / Sheep / reverse transcription-polymerase chain reaction (RT-PCR) / 16 Oct 2014 / Positive

Future reporting
The event is continuing. Weekly follow-up reports will be submitted.

[The location of these outbreaks can be seen on the interactive map included in the OIE report at the source URL above.]

